<br>
Oh, uhh, yea what pissed me off so much?  Oh just trying to figure out who the hell Dean is so I go to some Howard Dean homepage and this is what I see staring at me in the face.  No Bio, no stance on issues, just this crap....<br>
<br>
&quot;What you have done is amazing. <br>
<br>
With more than 280,000 contributors this year—and more than 52,000 new contributors (more than 128,000 total) in this quarter alone—we’ve now reached more than $14 million raised so far in the 4th quarter. And the most incredible thing is how we’ve done this—through everybody taking action and doing their part—through hundreds of thousands of contributions averaging nearly $100. This is the $100 revolution. <br>
<br>
Your response has been incredible. Last quarter we hit $14.8 million. No one has ever done that before—you made history by raising more than any other Democratic candidate for President in a single quarter. And because of what you’ve done so far, we’re likely to raise nearly $40 million for this year. No Democrat has ever done that before, either. <br>
<br>
But it’s critical that we don’t let up. Against any single candidate, we’d be fine. But because you’ve built the greatest grassroots campaign in history, the other candidates are reverting to a one and two state strategy, and trying to throw up roadblocks of cash in your way. We’re being flanked in Iowa by Gephardt and anti-Dean 527 groups, who are spending millions to bring us down. Then in New Hampshire John Kerry is pouring his own money into non-stop television ads to try and stop us. And Wes Clark and other candidates are waiting for us in South Carolina and Arizona and the 5 other states that come on February 3rd. All their money together is aimed at stopping our campaign, even as we need to focus on Washington State and Michigan and the other races beyond—and George Bush himself in the general election. <br>
<br>
And for those who doubt that we can match George Bush’s $200 million in special interest money through millions of Americans giving what they can, you only need to point to what you’ve done already—raising $40 million, more than any Democrat in history, in the year before a single vote has been cast. You’ve done that because there’s a new and different way to do things, and that’s what we represent—taking politics away from the status quo and putting it back in the hands of the people. <br>
<br>
Please, do everything you can now. Don’t let up. How far we go is up to you—this campaign is once again in your hands. Everything we’ve accomplished is on the line, and you have the power to make history right now. &quot;<br>
<br>
Joe Trippi<br>
Campaign Manager<br>
Dean for America<br>
